    "steps": [
        "For the lavender simple syrup, put half the lavender buds and all of the water in a ^saucepan$. Bring the mixture to a boil, then add the sugar. Lower the heat so it maintains a gentle boil. Stir until sugar is dissolved. Lower the heat to a simmer and allow to simmer for 15 minutes. Turn of the heat and add the remaining lavender buds. Let the mixture cool, then taste. Steep longer for a stronger taste. Strain out the buds.",
        "For the turmeric ginger simple syrup, heat the water and sugar in a small ^saucepan$ over medium heat. Stir until all of the sugar is dissolved, then add the turmeric, cinnamon, and cardamom. Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 7 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in the ginger. Allow the mixture cool and then strain.",
        "For the cardamom honey simple syrup, cut the cardamom pods halfway and add to ^saucepan$ with water. Bring the water to boil, then reduce to a very gentle simmer for 10 minutes. Add sugar and salt, while allowing to simmer for another 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add the cardamom powder. Stir and strain.",
        "For the pecan simple syrup, put the sugar and water in a ^saucepan$. Bring the mixture to boil, then add the pecans and salt. Let the mixture simmer for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and let the mixture cool. Strain the mixture.",
        "For espresso based drinks, I typically use 1.5 tsp of the lavender syrup, 2 tsp of the turmeric ginger syrup, 2 tsp of the cardamom honey syrup, and 2 tsp of the pecan syrup. Feel free to adjust based on taste."
     
    ],
